From: Syncloud <support@syncloud.it>
Subject: Add LDAP authentication and enable scoped multi-user libraries

When PHOTOPRISM_LDAP_ENABLED=true, photoprism's shared `entity.Auth`
binds the supplied credentials against the platform's slapd before
falling back to the upstream local-account flow. Hooks the same code
path used by both the web sign-in form and the WebDAV basic-auth
handler, so every syncloud client - web, PWA, third-party WebDAV - can
authenticate with the user's syncloud password without any per-device
app-password ceremony or OIDC ceremony. Non-admin syncloud users are
created as photoprism RoleUser with BasePath=users/<handle>, which
trips the per-user scoped-search branch in internal/entity/search and
gives each account an isolated library. Photoprism CE's UserRoles
whitelist and GrantDefaults map are extended to recognise RoleUser so
the account passes IsRegistered() and CanLogIn() ACL checks. Original
LDAP path is the syncloud cyberb fork's commit 1b9b9c8 rebased onto
upstream tag 260305-fad9d5395.

